pyVHDLParser.Token.Keywords¶

Classes

  • SpecificVHDLToken: Base-class for all specific tokens.

  • BoundaryToken: Token representing a boundary between (reserved) words.

  • BracketToken: Base-class for all bracket tokens: (, ), [, ], {, }, < and >.

  • RoundBracketToken: Base-class for all round bracket tokens: ( and ).

  • OpeningRoundBracketToken: Token representing an opening round bracket: (.

  • ClosingRoundBracketToken: Token representing a closing round bracket: ).

  • SquareBracketToken: Base-class for all square bracket tokens: [ and ].

  • OpeningSquareBracketToken: Token representing an square round bracket: [.

  • ClosingSquareBracketToken: Token representing a closing square bracket: ].

  • CurlyBracketToken: Base-class for all curly bracket tokens: { and }.

  • OpeningCurlyBracketToken: Token representing an opening curly bracket: {.

  • ClosingCurlyBracketToken: Token representing a closing curly bracket: }.

  • AngleBracketToken: Base-class for all angle bracket tokens: < and >.

  • OpeningAngleBracketToken: Token representing an opening angle bracket: <.

  • ClosingAngleBracketToken: Token representing a closing angle bracket: >.

  • OperatorToken: Base-class for all operator tokens.

  • PlusOperator: Token representing a plus operator: +.

  • MinusOperator: Token representing a minus operator: -.

  • MultiplyOperator: Token representing a multiply operator: *.

  • DivideOperator: Token representing a divide operator: /.

  • ModuloOperator: Base-class for all operator tokens.

  • RemainderOperator: Base-class for all operator tokens.

  • PowerOperator: Token representing a power operator: **.

  • ConcatOperator: Token representing a concat operator: &.

  • RelationalOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • EqualOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • UnequalOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • LessThanOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • LessThanOrEqualOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • GreaterThanOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • GreaterThanOrEqualOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • MatchingEqualOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • MatchingUnequalOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • MatchingLessThanOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • MatchingLessThanOrEqualOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • MatchingGreaterThanOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • MatchingGreaterThanOrEqualOperator: Base-class for all relational operator tokens.

  • DelimiterToken: Token representing a delimiter sign in between list items.

  • EndToken: Token representing an end of a statement.

  • IdentifierToken: Token representing an identifier.

  • RepeatedIdentifierToken: Token representing a repeated identifier.

  • SimpleNameToken: Base-class for all specific tokens.

  • LabelToken: Token representing a label.

  • RepeatedLabelToken: Token representing a repeated label.

  • MultiCharKeyword: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • CommentKeyword: Base-class for all comment keywords: --, /* and */.

  • SingleLineCommentKeyword: Token representing a starting sequence for a single-line comment: --.

  • MultiLineCommentKeyword: Base-class for all tokens related to multi-line comments: /* and */.

  • MultiLineCommentStartKeyword: Token representing a starting sequence for a multi-line comment: /*.

  • MultiLineCommentEndKeyword: Token representing a closing sequence for a multi-line comment: */.

  • AssignmentKeyword: Base-class for all assignment keywords: := and <=.

  • VariableAssignmentKeyword: Token representing a variable assignment: :=.

  • SignalAssignmentKeyword: Token representing a signal assignment: <=.

  • AssociationKeyword: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • MapAssociationKeyword: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • SignalAssociationKeyword: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • KeywordToken: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • DirectionKeyword: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • Operator: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • LogicalOperator: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • MiscellaneousOperator: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • ShiftOperator: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • AbsOperator: Reserved word ‘abs’ for unary operator absolute value.

  • AccessKeyword: Reserved word ‘access’ to defined access types.

  • AfterKeyword: Reserved word ‘after’.

  • AliasKeyword: Reserved word ‘alias’ to declare aliases.

  • AllKeyword: Reserved word ‘all’.

  • AndOperator: Reserved word ‘and’ for binary logical operator and.

  • ArchitectureKeyword: Reserved word ‘architecture’ to define architectures.

  • ArrayKeyword: Reserved word ‘array’ to define array types.

  • AssertKeyword: Reserved word ‘assert’ for assert-statements.

  • AttributeKeyword: Reserved word ‘attribute’.

  • BeginKeyword: Reserved word ‘begin’ to distinguish declarative regions from statements regions.

  • BlockKeyword: Reserved word ‘block’ for block-statements.

  • BodyKeyword: Reserved word ‘body’ to distinguish declarations from implementations (bodies).

  • BufferKeyword: Reserved word ‘buffer’ for mode buffer.

  • BusKeyword: Reserved word ‘bus’.

  • CaseKeyword: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • ComponentKeyword: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • ConfigurationKeyword: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

  • ConstantKeyword: Base-class for all VHDL specific tokens.

Classes

class pyVHDLParser.Token.Keywords.SpecificVHDLToken[source]¶

Base-class for all specific tokens.

Simple token will be converted to specific tokens while parsing. The internal data is copied, and the original token is replaced by this token.

Inheritance

__init__(previousToken=None, value=None, start=None, end=None, fromExistingToken=None)[source]¶

Initialize a specific token, by copying the simple token’s data and link this new token to the previous token as a replacement.

class pyVHDLParser.Token.Keywords.BoundaryToken[source]¶

Token representing a boundary between (reserved) words.

In many cases, a SpaceToken, CommentToken, LinebreakToken or CharacterToken becomes a BoundaryToken.
